---

<section id="about" class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="text-gold font-medium tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-sm mb-3">July 3, 2026</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">The Countdown Is On</h2>
      <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-red mx-auto"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Two column layout -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <!-- Text -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-lg text-slate leading-relaxed">
          Fifty years ago, Washington, D.C. stood at the center of one of the most memorable
          celebrations in American history: the Bicentennial of the United States. It was a moment
          of grandeur, pride, and patriotism that left an indelible mark on a generation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate leading-relaxed">
          July 4, 2026 marks the 250th anniversary of the United States of America. Proud Americans
          will celebrate this extraordinary moment from coast to coast. But the biggest celebration
          of all begins the night before in our nation's capital, when thousands gather to kick off
          the historic anniversary weekend at the All-American <span class="font-bold uppercase">Countdown 250</span> Ball.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg font-medium text-navy">
          Be there when history is made.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Image -->
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-xl aspect-[4/3]">
          <img
            src="/images/event/countdown-toast.png"
            alt="Guests raising champagne glasses during the midnight countdown"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover scale-[1.02]"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="absolute -bottom-4 -right-4 w-32 h-32 bg-navy/10 rounded-lg -z-10"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
